::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 504121001: Config/Level/Mission/5041210/Act/Act504121001.json-->
::'''"Dux Carminum" Verginia:''' Forging firewood from golden blood to burn away the gloom of the deep sea... feels too dry and lifeless.
::'''"Dux Carminum" Verginia:''' Then again... the sword-bloom blossoms in the song of the lyre, a requiem for the Titans before their fall... might be a bit too on the nose.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Another love poem, Dux Carminum?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504121004-->
::'''"Dux Carminum" Verginia:''' N&mdash;No, it's not, {{MC|m=Mr.|f=Miss}} (Trailblazer)! I've written enough love poems these days. I can't slack off on my job...
::'''"Dux Carminum" Verginia:''' I&mdash;I'm writing the ''Heroic Saga of Flame-Chase'', an epic poem about the Flame-Chase Journey.
::'''"Dux Carminum" Verginia:''' Still, maybe it's from indulging in too many toasts and banquets. It feels like my inspiration's been soaked and soured by honey brew. Every time I try to write a few lines, nothing ever seems quite right...
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} What if, I contribute a line?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504121008-->
::'''"Dux Carminum" Verginia:''' O&mdash;Of course! I was just writing about the fall of Phagousa. A champion like you... I'm sure you'll r&mdash;relate to experiencing that spectacular scenery!
